  "text": "Gene expression profiles have also been used for classification of tissues for disease diagnosis [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Classification methods are conceptually the same as gene clustering in the sense that the data analyses are conducted with rows and columns being transposed. Special techniques have been developed for tissue classification, for example, dimension reduction [CITATION_6] ) and variable selection [CITATION_7] .",
